metadata.name: Ringstind, Norway
metadata.description:
Ringstind is a mountain in the mountain chain named Hurrungane in Norway. Its a summit 2 124 meters above sea level.  A 6-8 hours backcountry ski session. 
I have been there once, and its one of the finest mountains I've been on to this date! You'll be meet by a fantastic view of Hurrungane, and you have a great view of the most famous mountain in the area, Store Skagastølstind. 
 
I love to go backcountry skiing during winter, and I aim to go this again this year(2022). Its almost 10 years ago last time I was there!
The photo was taken summer 2019, when me and my girlfriend(now wife) went roadtripping in the midst of Norway. I can recommend to anyone visiting Norway, to travel to Hurrungane in Sogn and Fjordane and see the mountains there. 

I took this photo summer 2019, with my Panasonic GH4, with my Leica 50mm, F 1.4

Location:
61°26′31″N 7°48′02″E
